{
  "_README": [
    "AUTHORED SYNTHETIC CALIBRATION CORPUS -- not external canon.",
    "Every sample in human/ and ai/ was written by hand for this eval to be",
    "representative of its class. No copyrighted text was copied. The 'human'",
    "samples are deliberately written in a genuine human voice (varied rhythm,",
    "real stance, concrete detail). The 'ai' samples are deliberately loaded",
    "with the classic AI-slop signature (filler, rule-of-three, bold-bullet",
    "listicles, hedging, puffery, meta-commentary, uniform rhythm).",
    "",
    "Because the samples were authored to exhibit (or avoid) exactly the tells",
    "the linter looks for, this corpus measures internal consistency and",
    "calibration -- NOT real-world detection accuracy on text in the wild.",
    "Treat the numbers as a floor sanity check, not a benchmark. See eval/EVAL.md.",
    "",
    "register values match the linter's --register choices where applicable",
    "(technical, business, marketing, academic, casual, creative, email).",
    "",
    "Binary classifier set: 58 files (34 human, 24 ai), balanced so every register",
    "has both classes. The two creative 'ai' samples lean on non-dash tells",
    "(filler, rule-of-three, antithesis, vacuity) because the creative register",
    "mutes the dash checks.",
    "",
    "Hard negatives carry a 'group' tag. esl_formal/ (10, label human, group esl)",
    "are careful non-native / formal-human samples that real detectors over-flag;",
    "they stay in the binary set and feed a dedicated ESL false-positive rate.",
    "over_corrected/ (10, label over_corrected) is the anti-AI costume -- text that",
    "SHOULD be flagged -- held out of the binary AUC and scored on its own recall."
  ],
